Two people died and three others were seriously injured when a bakkie and a car collided on the N2 on Wednesday. According to Shawn Herbst, Netcare 911 spokesperson, the accident happened just after 12 at noon on the N2 south-bound, near Joyner Road. “Reports indicate that a bakkie and car were involved in a collision resulting in both vehicles being torn apart,” he added. Two men had suffered fatal injuries and were declared dead at the scene. “Three other people had sustained moderate injuries and were treated on scene before being transported to hospital for further care,” Herbst said. Police are investigating the cause of the crash.